reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A GREAT BUY!
reviews.reviewText: I really love this shoe rack!! So much that I bought two of them!! VERY easy to put together and compact enough to fit behind my front door; yet those hold eight to ten pair of shoes each. Very good buy for the price.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 10, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars All I need
reviews.reviewText: This shoe rack is good for my needs. Not very sturdy but works for my shoes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 26, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It's not hard to assemble. Pretty good quality light weight but, was able to put two pairs of shoes for adults on each shelf and about four pairs of kids shoes on each rack. After you assembly easy to move and does not fall apart.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Very flimsy materials that break quickly
reviews.reviewText: Yes it is cheap and I shouldn’t have expected much, but the materials are so flimsy they break immediately. The “metal” bent as I was putting the rack together and the fabric/plastic that holds the shoes is so thin you can see through it. You’re better off spending a bit more for something functional.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 20, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This review is based entirely on this item by itself and not compared to wooden shoe racks.I didn't expect much when I ordered this. It's inexpensive and it's fabric, not wood. But the pieces fit together very well. It fits into the little corner I had available for it, and it fits into a closet. I am able to put two pairs of shoes on each shelf. It's providing me with a perfectly usable shoe rack while I think about what I want in the log run.You could also use this for purses, winter accessories or to toss your keys and wallet on.I'd recommend it for situations when you aren't going to have a wooden rack: college, studio apartments, people who don't know what they'll want in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Pieces do not fit together correct ly
reviews.reviewText: The shelf does not fit the pieces together properly. They had to be forced in some instances. It sits wobbly and it’s not very sturdy, but other than that it works fine.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Need this in the laundry room that comes in from the garage for our indoor and outdoor shoe.
reviews.reviewText: Very easy to put together and seems sturdy enough. I just needed a small shoe rack.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Easy to put together
reviews.reviewText: This was easy to put together. It didn't take long at all. I was not impressed with the pieces that your shoes sit on. I felt it was very thin and almost felt like thick paper. I am unsure how long it is going to last with constant use. We use it in the mud room where our shoes are wet from the heavy dew. It is a good size and fit in the room nicely.
